<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1059,973,1054]" pageId="2" pageNumber="937">
D i a g n o s i s: Black, poorly iridescent, almost matt. Laterally quite convex; dorsal outline oval, broad near the shoulders, quite strongly tapering toward the elytral apex (
<figureCitation box="[159,218,1032,1054]" captionStart="Figs 1-6" captionStartId="13.[151,191,1334,1354]" captionTargetBox="[169,1042,208,1241]" captionTargetId="figure-6@13.[151,1059,619,838]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Figs 1-6: Habitus of: (1) Hydrocanthus balkei; (2) H. pederzanii; (3) H. australasiae; (4) H. waterhousei; (5) indicus, f. typica; (6) indicus, black form (scale: 2 mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5434510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5434510/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="937">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1059,1069,1150]" pageId="2" pageNumber="937">
